          <td align="left" valign="bottom" nowrap width="490" height="30"><p><span class="mark">&diams; </span>Goals of the course</p>
            <p>The goals of this course are as follows: to deepen your recognition of Nagoya University and its students multilaterally, and to obtain information that will enable you to make use of Nagoya University skillfully to enrich your life as a student.  Specifically, the course is designed to deepen your understanding of the following issues:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>The ideal method of 'learning' changes as you progress from high school to university to members of society.</li>
              <li>Understanding of your university by examining facts and information regarding Nagoya University from different perspectives.</li>
              <li>The direction in which Nagoya University, which has just become an independent entity, intends to advance.</li>
              <li>Assessment of what the university ought to be from different perspectives.</li>
              <li>The attitudes of Japanese university students in general and, specifically, Nagoya University students, toward study.</li>
              <li>The development of university students as individuals.</li>
              <li>Learn the basic method for designing your own future.</li>
            </ul>  

            <p><span class="mark">&diams; </span>Textbook</p>
            <p>A "Course Packet," a compilation of data, is distributed to all students attending the course.  The course is conducted on the basis of this Course Packet.</p>
            
            <p><span class="mark">&diams;</span>Who can register in this course</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Students who wish to enhance their way of studying and enrich their life at the university.</li>
              <li>Students who are interested in the institution of Nagoya University.</li>
              <li>Students who are interested in what Nagoya University students think about and worry about.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p><span class="mark">&diams;</span>Note:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>This course is a joint project of the Higher Education Research Center and General Center for Student Consultation.</li>
              <li>During this course, experts and guest speakers from various fields are invited to provide opportunities for students to exchange views.  The course aims to offer interactive and attractive classes.</li>
              <li>This course uses an on-line system called 'Going Syllabus' to support students attending the course.  This system was developed by the Higher Education Research Center, Nagoya University, three years ago.  Using 'Going Syllabus,' you cannot only confirm the details of the syllabus but also download teaching materials used in the course, submit assignments, and hold discussions.  Operating the system is very easy.<br>See <a title="Going Syllabus" href="http://gs.cshe.nagoya-u.ac.jp/">http://gs.cshe.nagoya-u.ac.jp/</a></li>
</ul>
